article.headline: Vermont 77, Stony Brook 70
article.story: BURLINGTON, Vt. (AP) -- Taylor Coppenrath scored 30 points as Vermont held off Stony Brook, 77-70, at Patrick Gym Wednesday night. The nation's fifth leading scorer, Coppenrath went seven-for-nine from the floor and 15-for-18 from the free throw line. He scored 17 in the second half as the Catamounts improved to 5-0 in the America East and 8-5 overall. Both teams traded the lead six times in the first half before Vermont settled into a 33-31 lead at the break. Munir led Stony Brook(5-9, 2-3 America East) with 19 points going five-for-seven from three-point range. Spencer tallied 16 as did Mike Konopka, who was a perfect seven-for-seven from the floor.
